#
#WIKI MARKUP SYNTAX
#
#Pages use a simple text markup:
#
# *	Blank line starts a new paragraph
# *	A paragraph in ALL CAPS becomes a section heading
# *	Line starting with * is a bullet item
# *	Line starting with ! is preformatted (code)
# *	[page name] links to another wiki page
# *	[text | url] creates an external link
#
#PAGES
#
#Pages are created by the wiki agent (wiki9p) during ingest
#or by humans via the edit form in Charon.  Each page has
#full version history and conflict detection.
#
#Page types used by the knowledge base:
#
# *	Source summaries - distilled from ingested documents
# *	Concept pages - topic overviews synthesizing multiple sources
# *	Entity pages - specific things (products, organizations, standards)
# *	Synthesis pages - cross-cutting analysis across topics
# *	Lint reports - automated health checks
#

